## Force.com Naming Conventions

Here's a comprehensive set of naming conventions for the Force.com platform:

---

### Custom Objects & Fields

```
// Custom Objects - PascalCase, singular noun
MyObject__c
ProjectTask__c
CustomerAccount__c

// Custom Fields - PascalCase
MyObject__c.FirstName__c
MyObject__c.IsActive__c        // Boolean fields prefixed with 'Is'
MyObject__c.TotalAmount__c

// Junction Objects - combine both object names
ProjectTask__c (joining Project__c and Task__c)

// Relationship Fields
ParentObject__c    // Lookup/Master-Detail fields end with object name
```

---

### Apex Classes

```java
// Standard Classes - PascalCase, noun
public class OpportunityLineItem {}
public class ProjectTaskManager {}

// Controllers - suffix with 'Controller'
public class ProjectTaskController {}
public class MyObjectController {}

// Controller Extensions - suffix with 'Extension'  
public class ProjectTaskExtension {}

// Test Classes - suffix with 'Test'
public class ProjectTaskControllerTest {}
public class ProjectTaskManagerTest {}

// Batch Classes - suffix with 'Batch'
public class LeadProcessingBatch implements Database.Batchable<sObject> {}

// Scheduler Classes - suffix with 'Scheduler'
public class LeadProcessingScheduler implements Schedulable {}

// Queueable Classes - suffix with 'Queueable'
public class LeadProcessingQueueable implements Queueable {}

// Trigger Handlers - suffix with 'TriggerHandler'
public class OpportunityTriggerHandler {}

// Service Classes - suffix with 'Service'
public class OpportunityService {}

// Selector/Query Classes - suffix with 'Selector'
public class OpportunitySelector {}

// Utility/Helper Classes - suffix with 'Util' or 'Helper'
public class DateUtil {}
public class StringHelper {}

// Exception Classes - suffix with 'Exception'
public class InvalidInputException extends Exception {}

// Wrapper Classes - suffix with 'Wrapper' or 'DTO'
public class OpportunityWrapper {}
public class OpportunityDTO {}

// Interface - prefix with 'I'
public interface IOpportunityService {}
```

---

### Apex Methods

```java
public class OpportunityService {

    // Standard methods - camelCase, start with verb
    public void processOpportunities() {}
    public List<Opportunity> getOpenOpportunities() {}
    public Boolean isValidOpportunity() {}
    public Opportunity buildOpportunity() {}

    // Test methods - prefix with 'test'
    @isTest
    static void testGetOpenOpportunities() {}

    // Test data factory methods
    @isTest
    static void setupTestData() {}
}
```

---

### Apex Variables & Constants

```java
public class OpportunityService {

    // Constants - UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
    private static final Integer MAX_RECORDS = 200;
    private static final String DEFAULT_STATUS = 'New';

    // Static variables - camelCase
    private static Integer recordCount;

    // Instance variables - camelCase
    private String opportunityName;
    private Boolean isProcessed;

    // Collections - plural camelCase
