| Step | What happens |
|------|-------------|
| `arr.map(async ...)` | Returns `Promise<number>[]` (array of promises) |
| `Promise.all(...)` | Converts `Promise<number>[]` → `Promise<number[]>` |
| `await Promise.all(...)` | Resolves to `number[]` ✅ |

## How `Promise.all` Works

```typescript
// Promise.all runs all promises concurrently and waits for ALL to resolve
const [result1, result2] = await Promise.all([
    Promise.resolve(1),  // resolves to 1
    Promise.resolve(2),  // resolves to 2
]);
// result1 = 1, result2 = 2
```

