- `async` functions **always** return a `Promise`, so `arr.map(async ...)` will always produce `Promise[]`
- Use **`Promise.all`** when you want concurrent execution and need all results
- Use a **`for...of` loop** when you need sequential execution
- Use **`Promise.allSettled`** when you want to handle individual promise failures

